1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,600
When oceans get too warm, corals evict their partners — and turn ghostly white.

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:10,000
Corals rely on tiny algae called zooxanthellae, which live inside them.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,800
This relationship is crucial for their survival.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:19,200
But when temperatures rise, corals stress out and kick out these vital partners, leading to bleaching.

5
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:24,400
According to NOAA, while some corals can recover, repeated heat stress increases mortality.

6
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:28,000
The fate of coral reefs rests on our actions.

7
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,200
Protecting our oceans is essential for their survival.

8
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:34,000
Want to learn more about ocean health?

9
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,800
Follow for more insights on climate change!
